text: Justin Dec made such a masterpiece of a film that had many new and intuitive techniques for the horror genre that made it a great breath of fresh air. Some movies have tried and failed miserably to tackle modern horror such as both Unfriended movies or even One missed call and it's horrible CGI. I found Countdown to have great special effects especially for having just a 6.5 million budget. Its true that there were still some cliche aspects about it but what I absolutely loved was there was no annoying loud noises/ loud music during the jump scares as well as a great build up with the suspense. Looking forward to 2.0 if they ever make it! Both actresses, Elizabeth Lail and Talitha Bateman carried this film with their great acting.
